{"title_hebrew":"שבורי לב","title_english":"Shvurei Lev (Brokenhearted)","artist":"Hanan Ben Ari","overview":"A deeply spiritual cry asking who truly understands pain and who can heal a broken heart. It reflects a longing for God's embrace and a promise that one will not surrender to despair.","youtube_url":"https://youtu.be/z27MZP_4P_U?si=fBmHDmy89Iv6tEBB","lyrics":[{"hebrew":"מִי יוֹדֵעַ כָּל כְּאֵב","transliteration":"Mi yodea kol ke'ev","english":"Who knows every pain"},{"hebrew":"מִי רוֹפֵא לִשְׁבוּרֵי לֵב","transliteration":"Mi rofe lishvurei lev","english":"Who is a doctor for the brokenhearted"},{"hebrew":"יוֹצֵר אוֹר וָחֹשֶׁךְ","transliteration":"Yotzer or vechoshech","english":"Creator of light and darkness"},{"hebrew":"עוֹשֶׂה שָׁלוֹם וּמִלְחָמָה","transliteration":"Ose shalom umilchama","english":"Maker of peace and war"},{"hebrew":"מִי יוֹשֵׁב עַל כִּסֵּא דִּין","transliteration":"Mi yoshev al kise din","english":"Who sits on the throne of judgment"},{"hebrew":"מִתְכַּסֶּה בָּרַחֲמִים","transliteration":"Mitkase barachamim","english":"Covers Himself in mercy"},{"hebrew":"מוֹחֵל וְסוֹלֵחַ","transliteration":"Mochel vesoleach","english":"Pardons and forgives"},{"hebrew":"מַבִּיט וְיוֹדֵעַ","transliteration":"Mabit veyodea","english":"Looks and knows"},{"hebrew":"וּמִי יְרַפֵּא לִבִּי","transliteration":"Umi yerape libi","english":"And who will heal my heart"},{"hebrew":"אֶל מִי אֲנִי מִתְגַּעְגֵּעַ","transliteration":"El mi ani mitga'agea","english":"For whom do I yearn"},{"hebrew":"כְּמוֹ יָם שֶׁאֵין לוֹ חוֹף","transliteration":"Kmo yam she'ein lo chof","english":"Like a sea that has no shore"},{"hebrew":"רַק תַּגִּיד לִי מִי","transliteration":"Rak tagid li mi","english":"Just tell me who"},{"hebrew":"מִי יְחַבֵּק אוֹתִי וְיַבְטִיחַ","transliteration":"Mi yechabek oti veyavtiach","english":"Who will hug me and promise"},{"hebrew":"שֶׁאֲנִי לֹא אֶכָּנַע בַּסּוֹף","transliteration":"She'ani lo ekana basof","english":"That I will not surrender in the end"},{"hebrew":"מִי הָיָה הֹוֶה וְיִהְיֶה","transliteration":"Mi haya hove veyihye","english":"Who was, is, and will be"},{"hebrew":"מִי מֵמִית וּמֵחַיֵּה","transliteration":"Mi memit umechaye","english":"Who brings death and gives life"},{"hebrew":"פּוֹתֵחַ יָדַיִם","transliteration":"Poteach yadayim","english":"Opens His hands"},{"hebrew":"מַצְמִיחַ כְּנָפַיִם","transliteration":"Matzmiach knafayim","english":"Grows wings"}]}